prompt: Create a 1950s American retro comic book illustration designed as an EDUCATIONAL INSERT panel in the style of a vintage science diagram with bold black ink outlines, flat saturated colors, and clear explanatory visual elements. The panel shows a side-by-side comparison of TWO BATTERY GAUGES representing INTROVERT and EXTROVERT energy dynamics in social situations. On the LEFT side, an "EXTROVERT BATTERY" is shown with an UPWARD arrow during social interaction - the battery is FILLING UP, going from 60% toward 90%, with a happy face indicator. The label reads "SOCIAL INTERACTION → GAINS ENERGY." Small icons show crowds, handshakes, conversations all adding to the battery. On the RIGHT side, an "INTROVERT BATTERY" is shown with a DOWNWARD arrow during the SAME social interaction - the battery is DRAINING, going from 60% toward 20%, with a stressed face indicator. The label reads "SOCIAL INTERACTION → SPENDS ENERGY." The same crowd icons are shown, but each one removes energy from the battery. A large caption box at the top reads: "INTROVERSION vs EXTROVERSION: ENERGY DYNAMICS" A key insight box at the bottom reads: "Neither is better. Both need to understand their pattern." Another science note explains: "Introverts have higher baseline cortical arousal. Social stimulation easily tips them into overstimulation. Extroverts have lower baseline arousal and NEED social stimulation to reach optimal levels. Knowing your type determines your recharge strategy." The visual style uses clear battery metaphor iconography, contrasting colors (green for filling, red for draining), vintage educational comic aesthetic, bold lines, and informative design that teaches the core concept visually., high quality, soft professional lighting, well-composed
